## ML Integration

[mlService.js](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/backend/services/mlService.js) uses an Axios client pre-configured with `ML_API_URL` from `.env`:

- [detectRisk(patientData)](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/backend/services/mlService.js#9-18) → `POST /api/v1/risk-detection`
- [clusterHouses(houses)](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/backend/services/mlService.js#19-28) → `POST /api/v1/cluster-houses`

If the ML service is unavailable, patient records are saved gracefully without a risk result.

